headline:
Imps set to benefit from Reemstma buy: COMPANIES DIARY: TODAY: * Imperial
Tobacco's profits are expected to jump from Pounds 509m to approaching Pounds
620m for the year to September 30, reflecting the initial contribution from the
Pounds 3.6bn acquisition of Reemstma in March. In September the group said it
had cut 800 jobs since buying the German cigarette maker, and it was planning to
shed another 800 from its 18,000-strong global workforce. The group also said it
was on target to deliver Pounds 170m of annual cost savings from integrating
Reemstma, and that its share of the UK cigarette market, excluding its
distribution of Philip Morris's Marlboro, had risen from 39.6 to 42.9 per cent
in the 11 months to August.: TUESDAY: * National Grid Transco, Britain's biggest
utility, reports its first interim figures since the merger between the high
voltage transmission operator and the Transco national gas pipeline network was
completed last month.
